    • Flight

      public Flight​(int id, java.lang.String flightNumber, java.lang.String origin, java.lang.String destination, java.time.LocalDate departureDate, int seats, float price, boolean isDeleted)
      Second Constructor, identical to the first, but has the extra boolean property isDeleted - having 2 constructors so when loading the data from the file, it saves/keeps track of its state regarding if it has been deleted or not and to do this, the second constructor will be used to initialise the already existing object instead of the first. As the first constructor will be used to create a new flight.
      Parameters:
      isDeleted - boolean representing if the flight has been deleted/removed from the FBS.
      id - integer representing the flights unique ID.
      flightNumber - String representing the flight number of the flight.
      origin - String representing where the flight will take off from.
      destination - String representing the destination of the flight.
      departureDate - LocalDate representing when the flight will take place.
      seats - integer representing amount of seats the flight has.
      price - float representing the cost to book this flight.
